%T A394212 24,14,65,64,62,58,53,45,35,21,80,79,77,73,68,60,50,36,15,96,95,93,89,
%U A394212 84,76,66,52,31,16,122,121,119,115,110,102
%N A394212 Difference set of Mian-Chowla sequence in order of appearance.
%C A394212 Given by a greedy algorithm which constructs the Mian-Chowla sequence by taking an integer and checking whether its differences already occur in the difference set and then adding them to it.
%C A394212 It is not known whether it contains all positive integers or not. The least unknown number is 33.
%C A394212 The behavior of the sequence is cascade-like and is best seen by examining its difference sequence, which gives A394213.
%H A394212 Sean A. Irvine, <a href="/A394212/b394212.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A394212 Thomas Bloom, <a href="https://www.erdosproblems.com/340">Problem 340</a>, Erdős Problems.
%e A394212 1 = 2 - 1; 3 = 4 - 1; 2 = 4 - 2.
%Y A394212 Difference set of A005282. See A394213 and A394214.
%K A394212 nonn
%O A394212 1,2
